pitt.search.semanticvectors

Enum Search.SearchType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Search.SearchType>
      • pitt.search.semanticvectors.Search.SearchType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Search.SearchType>
    Enclosing class:
    Search

    public static enum Search.SearchType
extends Enum<Search.SearchType>
    Different types of searches that can be performed, set using FlagConfig.searchtype().

    Most involve processing combinations of vectors in different ways, in building a query expression, scoring candidates against these query expressions, or both. Most options here correspond directly to a particular subclass of VectorSearcher.

    Names may be passed as command-line arguments, so underscores are avoided.

      PRINTQUERY
      Builds an additive query vector (as with SUM and prints out the query vector for debugging).
      SUBSPACE
      "Quantum disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, create a representation for the subspace spanned by these vectors, and score by measuring cosine similarity with this subspace.
      SUM
      Build a query by adding together (weighted) vectors for each of the query terms, and search using cosine similarity.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SUM

        public static final Search.SearchType SUM
        Build a query by adding together (weighted) vectors for each of the query terms, and search using cosine similarity. See VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherCosine. This is the default search option.

      • SUBSPACE

        public static final Search.SearchType SUBSPACE
        "Quantum disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, create a representation for the subspace spanned by these vectors, and score by measuring cosine similarity with this subspace. Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherSubspaceSim.

      • MAXSIM

        public static final Search.SearchType MAXSIM
        "Closest disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, score by measuring distance to each term and taking the minimum. Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherMaxSim.

      • MINSIM

        public static final Search.SearchType MINSIM
        "Farthest conjunction" - get vectors for each query term, score by measuring distance to each term and taking the maximum. Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherMaxSim.

      • PERMUTATION

        public static final Search.SearchType PERMUTATION
        Uses permutation of coordinates to model typed relationships, as introduced by Sahlgren at al. (2008).

        Searches for the term that best matches the position of a "?" in a sequence of terms. For example martin ? king should retrieve luther as the top ranked match.

        Requires FlagConfig.queryvectorfile() to contain unpermuted vectors, either random vectors or previously learned term vectors, and FlagConfig.searchvectorfile() must contain permuted learned vectors.

        Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherPerm.

      • BALANCEDPERMUTATION

        public static final Search.SearchType BALANCEDPERMUTATION
        This is a variant of the PERMUTATION method which takes the mean of the two possible search directions (search with index vectors for permuted vectors, or vice versa). Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherPerm.

      • BOUNDPRODUCT

        public static final Search.SearchType BOUNDPRODUCT
        Used for Predication Semantic Indexing, see PSI. Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherBoundProduct.

      • LUCENE

        public static final Search.SearchType LUCENE
        Lucene document search, for comparison.

      • BOUNDMINIMUM

        public static final Search.SearchType BOUNDMINIMUM
        Used for Predication Semantic Indexing, see PSI. Finds minimum similarity across query terms to seek middle terms

      • BOUNDPRODUCTSUBSPACE

        public static final Search.SearchType BOUNDPRODUCTSUBSPACE
        Binds vectors to facilitate search across multiple relationship paths. Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherBoundProductSubSpace

      • INTERSECTION

        public static final Search.SearchType INTERSECTION
        Uses intersection between supplied predicate_concept combinations Implemented for binary vectors only currently Uses VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherBoundProductSubSpace

      • ANALOGY

        public static final Search.SearchType ANALOGY
        Intended to support searches of the form A is to B as C is to ?, but hasn't worked well thus far. (dwiddows, 2013-02-03).

      • PRINTQUERY

        public static final Search.SearchType PRINTQUERY
        Builds an additive query vector (as with SUM and prints out the query vector for debugging).
